**Topic: AI-assisted Backup Operations within Current Tooling Boundaries**

Gaia/Glean is a valid Cohesity-native AI direction for protected-data search and summarization, but it should remain future scope because licensing/entitlement and implementation need to be confirmed separately. For the current phase, we should stay within available capabilities: Cohesity DataProtect, read-only Cohesity APIs, ServiceNow integration, and Claude Code for controlled script/API development.

| Sl no | Tower                    | Task Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 | Which AI tool will handle it more efficiently and why?                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  | Next Step: High level solution approach                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        | Benefits / ROI                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ----: | ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
|     1 | Backup / Data Protection | Selective AI-assisted incident enrichment and SOP-based triage support for Cohesity DataProtect backup failures and infrastructure alerts such as interface failures, power supply alerts, source health issues, and repeated workload failures. | **Claude Code** can be used within approved risk/control boundaries to accelerate development of read-only Cohesity API scripts, ServiceNow enrichment logic, SOP mapping, and standard incident notes. This does not replace Cohesity or ServiceNow; it helps build controlled automation around them. | Implement Cohesity-to-ServiceNow integration for selected alert/failure categories. Use read-only Cohesity APIs to collect affected object, protection group, cluster, source, run ID, last successful backup, failure reason, alert context, SOP reference, probable owner team, and recommended first checks. Start with high-value cases only, such as repeated failures, Oracle gaps, interface down alerts, power supply failures, source connectivity issues, and failures requiring backup-team triage. | Reduces alert noise, avoids duplicate routing where teams already receive alerts, improves ticket quality, speeds correct assignment, supports SOP-based action, reduces manual triage effort, lowers MTTR, and creates better audit evidence without immediate Gaia/Glean licensing dependency. |
